# Testing Conventions

## Three-layer strategy

| Layer | Tool | Location | Naming |
|-------|------|----------|--------|
| Unit | Vitest | `features/<f>/__tests__/<name>.test.ts` | Pure functions, data helpers |
| Component | Vitest + RTL | `features/<f>/__tests__/<Component>.test.tsx` | React components |
| E2E | Playwright | `e2e/<feature>.spec.ts` | Full browser flows |

## Unit & component tests (Vitest)

Mock `next/navigation`:

```ts
vi.mock("next/navigation", () => ({
  useRouter: vi.fn(() => ({ push: vi.fn() })),
  usePathname: vi.fn(() => "/"),
  useSearchParams: vi.fn(() => new URLSearchParams()),
}));
```

Mock `next/link`:

```ts
vi.mock("next/link", () => ({
  default: ({ children, href }: any) => <a href={href}>{children}</a>,
}));
```

- Prefer `screen.getByRole`, `screen.getByText`, `screen.getByPlaceholderText` over `querySelector`.
- Import from barrel exports in tests: `import { DjCard } from "@/features/search"`.

## E2E tests (Playwright)

- Use `page.getByRole()` and `page.getByText("text", { exact: true })` to avoid strict mode violations.
- One spec file per route/feature.
- Playwright auto-starts the dev server via `webServer` config — do not start `npm run dev` manually.

## Scripts

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `npm test` | Unit + component (Vitest) |
| `npm run test:watch` | Vitest watch mode |
| `npm run test:e2e` | E2E (Playwright) |
| `npm run test:all` | Full suite |

## Baseline

65 Vitest + 19 Playwright = 84 tests, all passing. Do not regress.
